text:
Aroma - floral, very heavy caramel;
Appearance - deep copper, slightly hazy, thick fluffy head, excellent lacing;
Taste - caramel malt front, bold hop flavor blends into the back, mild bitterness, long balanced finish with a faint tang;
Palate - light crispness, pretty nice body;
Overall - meant to be savored, a must on any beer lovers bucket list.

12 oz. bottle

Aroma: really heavy malt, moderate to heavy hops and biscuity yeast, slight ginger highlights with definite brown sugar and maple syrup taste, maybe a hint of pine resin;

Appearance: large rocky, off-white fully lasting head with excellent lacing, hazy (small particulate matter) orange colour;

Taste: moderate bitterness with acidic and bitter finish;

Palate: full body, dry texture, lively carbonation and astringent finish;

Overall: A Rube Goldbergesque brew - eccentric and special. Yer lucky to get it.
